}</span><span class=\"w\">\n</span></code></pre></div></div>\n\n<h2 id=\"schema-design-notes\">Schema design notes</h2>\n\n<p>The current schema is shaped this way for pragmatic reasons:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>ids, titles, and hrefs are present so the browser can render useful results without secondary fetches</li>\n  <li>compact structured metadata is included so search can grow beyond exact title lookup</li>\n  <li><code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">search_terms</code> and <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">search_text</code> are precomputed so the browser does not need to reconstruct token bundles from heterogeneous fields on every search</li>\n  <li>the index stays compact by excluding full content bodies and other large page data</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"further-refinement\">Further Refinement</h2>\n\n<h2 id=\"out-of-scope-for-this-document\">Out of scope for this document</h2>\n\n<p>This document does not define:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>query normalization rules</li>\n  <li>scoring and ranking</li>\n  <li>result rendering behaviour</li>\n  <li>keyboard or interaction behaviour</li>\n  <li>detailed build steps</li>\n</ul>\n"
